What an honor to be invited to write an essay on Richard Avedon’s impact on my work for the new issue of the Financial Times How to Spend It magazine. In it I reflect on the creative friendship between Avedon and James Baldwin, and the indelible mark that Avedon’s work left on the medium of photography.

On the occasion of the ‘Avedon 100’ exhibition at @gagosian which opens tonight, I selected this little seen ‘mirror selfie’ of Avedon and Baldwin together in Baldwin’s mother’s Harlem home at the tender ages of 23 and 22. To me it signifies the importance of intimate creative friendships throughout the process of making and growing, creating and evolving.

Thank you to @avedonfoundation, @jellison22, and @gagosian for trusting me with this.

Read the essay at the link in my stories and see you tonight at the opening 🖤

My exhibition, Domestic Imaginaries, which features a new body of work, is now open at the SCAD Museum of Art in Savannah, Georgia. It means so much to mount this show in my home state. 

The show features a new laundry line installation which zig-zags down the nearly 300 foot length of the gallery and newly completed Altar sculptures which take after historical furniture shapes.

This show is a personal meditation on the role of domesticity, refuge, memory, textiles and nature in relationship to Black life.

It will be up until December 31, 2023 if you're in the Southern US make sure to go visit!

Thank you to my team and to Chief Curator of SCAD MoA @ddotpalmer for all the collaboration all along the way in making these new ambitious works which expand my practice and the ways that images can tell stories.
